\section sec_install_hoomd_mac Installing HOOMD-blue in Mac OS X

 -# <b>Download</b> the NVIDIA CUDA Toolkit appropriate for your system from http://www.nvidia.com/object/cuda_get.html . 
    <br><b>To install</b>, open Finder, navigate to the directory where you downloaded the file and double-click on it.
    Follow the on screen prompts to complete the installation.
    <br><br>
 -# (if you have an NVIDIA GPU) <b>Download</b> the CUDA drivers for your GPU from http://www.nvidia.com/object/cuda_get.html . 
    <br><b>To install</b>, open Finder, navigate to the directory where you downloaded the file and double-click on it.
    Follow the on screen prompts to complete the installation.
    <br><br>
 -# <b>Download</b> the HOOMD-blue package from http://codeblue.umich.edu/hoomd-blue/download.html
    <br><b>To install</b> to your <i>home directory</i>, open a terminal, cd to the directory where you downloaded the file
    and then run
 	\code
 tar -xvjpf hoomd-0.8.2-*.tar.bz2 -C ~/
 	\endcode
 	in a terminal. To <i>instead</i> install in a system directory for all users to access, extract into /opt by running
  	\code
 sudo tar -xvjpf hoomd-0.8.2-*.tar.bz2 -C /opt
    \endcode
    Then run
    \code
 open ~/.bash_profile
    \endcode
    <b>To open</b> your ~/.bash_profile file.  Add this line to the end:
    \code
 export PATH=${PATH}:${HOME}/hoomd-0.8.2-Darwin-i386-Python2.5/bin
    \endcode
    <i>Adjust</i> the name of the directory to <b>match the one you installed</b>.
    The path setting will only take effect in newly opened terminal windows.

\b Note: When upgrading to a new version of HOOMD-blue, update the lines you have already added to ~/.bash_profile 
instead of adding new ones.

